{{zh-hanzi|[[阿山]]}}
==Min Nan==
===Etymology===
A slang term originally derived from the middle character of [[唐山人]].  [[阿]] is used to describe a person in the familiar sense.

===Noun===
{{nan-noun|p|pojt=a1soaN1|tas=阿山|rs=阜05}}
# (''Taiwanese Min Nan'') [[w:mainlanders#Chinese mainlanders (Taiwan)|mainlanders]]

===Usage notes===
an old-fashioned term that was primarily used to describe non-[[w:Hoklo people|Hoklo people]] from Mainland China, a large number of whom had emmigrated to Taiwan after 1949.  This term later came to be replaced by [[gōa-séng-lâng]] ([[外省人]]).

